# AccessAI - local secrets (Phase 6: cloud VLM scene description + OCR)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to ".env" (which is git-ignored) and paste your real keys:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# GITHUB_MODELS_KEYS is a COMMA-SEPARATED list of GitHub Personal Access
# Tokens (PATs) that have "Models" access. Multiple keys enable automatic
# FAILOVER: when one key hits the free-tier rate limit (HTTP 429), AccessAI
# transparently retries the next one. One key works fine; two+ is sturdier.
#
# How to create a key:
#   1. GitHub -> Settings -> Developer settings -> Personal access tokens
#      -> Fine-grained tokens -> Generate new token.
#   2. Under "Permissions", grant the read-only "Models" permission.
#      (Fine-grained PATs with Models access are all that's required; no repo
#       or account scopes are needed.)
#   3. Copy the token (starts with github_pat_...) and paste it below.
#   4. For failover, make a second token (ideally on a second GitHub account)
#      and append it after a comma.
#
# NEVER commit real keys. This file (.env.example) holds only placeholders;
# the real .env is ignored by git. AccessAI masks keys to their last 4 chars
# in every log line and in the /vlm_status endpoint.

GITHUB_MODELS_KEYS=github_pat_REPLACE_ME_1,github_pat_REPLACE_ME_2
